<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,258,2080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A." box="[136,363,258,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="204 - 208" refId="ref6719" refString="Van de Beek, A. (1979) Taxonomie en nomenclatuur van de Koebraam. Gorteria 9: 204 - 208." type="journal article" year="1979">Van de Beek (1979)</bibRefCitation>
argued that 
<taxonomicName authority="Pourret (1788: 326)" authorityName="Pourret" authorityPageNumber="326" authorityYear="1788" box="[506,855,258,285]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[506,623,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. inermis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pourret, P. A." box="[631,855,258,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="297 - 334" refId="ref6052" refString="Pourret, P. A. (1788) Extrait de la Chloris Narbonensis. Histoire et Memoires de l'Academie de Toulouse 3: 297 - 334." type="journal article" year="1788">Pourret (1788: 326)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is identical with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1053,1198,258,284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[1053,1198,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because this name is earlier than 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[270,412,293,319]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[270,412,293,319]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it would be the correct name of the species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Monasterio-Huelin, E. &amp; Weber, H. E." box="[911,1313,293,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="311 - 322" refId="ref5806" refString="Monasterio-Huelin, E. &amp; Weber, H. E. (1996) Taxonomy and nomenclature of Rubus ulmifolius and Rubus sanctus (Rosaceae). Edinburgh Journal of Botany 33: 311 - 322. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0960428600003759" type="journal article" year="1996">Monasterio-Huelin &amp; Weber (1996)</bibRefCitation>
doubted the identity of both and claimed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[516,632,329,354]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[516,632,329,354]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be a hybrid of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[883,1028,329,355]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[883,1028,329,355]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1094,1197,329,355]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pourret" authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[1237,1447,329,355]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[1237,1354,329,354]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. inermis</emphasis>
Pourret
</taxonomicName>
, published in 
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A." box="[276,550,364,391]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="204 - 208" refId="ref6719" refString="Van de Beek, A. (1979) Taxonomie en nomenclatuur van de Koebraam. Gorteria 9: 204 - 208." type="journal article" year="1979">Van de Beek (1979: 206)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<emphasis box="[559,706,364,390]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Pourret 3168</emphasis>
(MAF-POURR), looks like a normal 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1119,1260,364,390]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[1119,1260,364,390]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without prickles, but hybrids can sometimes be very similar. However, the type does not show reduced fertility. This is confirmed by two other specimens of Pourret which were found after the publication of the type.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,258,2080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3391157304" collectionCode="P" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" specimenCode="P02521232" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
Another specimen (probably a duplicate of the 
<typeStatus box="[701,806,469,496]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">lectotype</typeStatus>
) was found at 
<collectionCode box="[961,976,470,496]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
(with barcode 
<specimenCode box="[1138,1268,469,496]" collectionCode="P" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" type="Herbarium">P02521232</specimenCode>
, image available at http://mediaphoto.mnhn.fr/media/1441338624753ZJhEBLGDiQxlEGfy). It consists of two unarmed inflorescences, with leaves and flowers, and clearly has young fruits that are not defective. At the base the sheet is annotated with “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[146,314,575,601]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">Rubus inermis</taxonomicName>
” by Pourret, and also contains a label annotated as “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[901,1066,575,601]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">Rubus inermis</taxonomicName>
<collectionCode box="[1073,1089,576,602]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
. / Caule fruticoso sub-rotundo. / Folis ternatis subtus tomentosis / an Canadensis. [handwritten by Pourret] / Pourret scripsit. [handwritten by Spach] / à Barcelona [handwritten by Pourret]”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,258,2080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">
The best specimen is preserved in the Salvador herbarium at BC (BC-Salvador 3833). It consists of both an inflorescence and a young primocane with leaves (
<figureCitation box="[712,783,716,742]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1928,1950]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-34@6.[151,1436,190,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Specimen of Rubus inermis Pourret preserved in the Salvador herbarium at BC (BC-Salvador 3833). Image courtesy of the herbarium BC, reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585408/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). It looks like a normal 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1058,1202,716,742]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[1058,1202,716,742]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without prickles. The Salvador family was a lineage of apothecaries who settled in Barcelona from the early 17th to the mid-19th century. The Salvador herbarium is the oldest and best-documented pre-Linnaean one in 
<collectingCountry box="[1054,1121,786,812]" name="Spain" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Spain</collectingCountry>
. Its labels bear pre-Linnaean names used in the works of Tournefort, Bauhin, Lobel, Dodoens, Magnol or Clusius, among others (
<bibRefCitation author="Ibanez, N. &amp; Montserrat, J. M. &amp; Soriano, I. &amp; Camarasa, J. M." pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="241 - 248" refId="ref5338" refString="Ibanez, N., Montserrat, J. M., Soriano, I. &amp; Camarasa, J. M. (2006) Plant material exchanged between James Petiver (ca. 1663 - 1718) and Joan Salvador i Riera (1683 - 1725). I. The Balearic plants conserved in the BC-Salvador and BM Sloane herbaria. Notes and Records. The Royal Society Journal of the History of Sciences 60: 241 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.1098 / rsnr. 2006.0148" type="journal article" year="2006">
Ibáñez 
<emphasis box="[1392,1452,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ibanez, N. &amp; Montserrat, J. M. &amp; Soriano, I." box="[205,266,857,883]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="633 - 636" refId="ref5433" refString="Ibanez, N., Montserrat, J. M. &amp; Soriano, I. (2008) Type specimens of names of species authored by Pourret conserved in the Salvador herbarium (BC). Taxon 57 (2): 633 - 636." type="journal article" year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
). Around 1782, the collection was revised for the first time by Pierre André Pourret (1754–1818), a French clergyman who lived in exile in 
<collectingCountry box="[507,571,892,918]" name="Spain" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Spain</collectingCountry>
at Santiago de Compostela from 1789 until his death (
<bibRefCitation author="Timbal-Lagrave, M. E." box="[1197,1447,892,919]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" refId="ref6347" refString="Timbal-Lagrave, M. E. (1875) Reliquiae Pourretianae. Au Secretariat General de la Societe des Sciences Physiques et Naturelles, Toulouse, 148 pp." type="book" year="1875">Timbal-Lagrave 1875</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Colmeiro, M." box="[136,308,927,953]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="289 - 292" refId="ref4993" refString="Colmeiro, M. (1891) Noticia de los trabajos botanicos del abate Pourret en Francia y Espana. Semanario Farmaceutico 35: 289 - 292." type="journal article" year="1891">Colmeiro 1891</bibRefCitation>
). Pourret added the Linnaean names of the species to the labels of the collection (
<bibRefCitation author="Camarasa, J. M." box="[1199,1376,927,953]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" refId="ref4914" refString="Camarasa, J. M. (1989) Botanica i botanics dels Paisos Catalans. Enciclopedia Catalana, Barcelona, 268 pp." type="book" year="1989">Camarasa 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Camarasa, J. M. &amp; Ibanez, N." box="[1386,1444,927,953]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="140 - 173" refId="ref4938" refString="Camarasa, J. M. &amp; Ibanez, N. (2007) Joan Salvador and James Petiver: a scientific correspondence (1706 - 1714) in time of wars. Archives of Natural History 34: 140 - 173. https: // doi. org / 10.3366 / anh. 2007.34.1.140" type="journal article" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
) and, in some cases, took out duplicates for his own herbarium (
<bibRefCitation author="Bolos, A." box="[833,966,962,989]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref4839" refString="Bolos, A. (1946) El Herbario Salvador. Collectanea Botanica (Barcelona) 1: 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1946">Bolòs 1946</bibRefCitation>
), now conserved in MAF as an independent historical collection (
<bibRefCitation author="Gutierrez-Bustillo, M. &amp; Navarro Aranda, C." box="[372,860,997,1024]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="193 - 195" refId="ref5283" refString="Gutierrez-Bustillo, M. &amp; Navarro Aranda, C. (1989) El herbario de P. A. Pourret (1754 - 1818) conservado en MAF. Acta Botanica Malacitana 14: 193 - 195. https: // doi. org / 10.24310 / abm. v 14 i. 9372" type="journal article" year="1989">Gutiérrez-Bustillo &amp; Navarro Aranda 1989</bibRefCitation>
). Some specimens in MAF-POURRET coming from the Salvador herbarium are among the most interesting in this collection. They can be easily recognized through the word “Salv” on the label, indicating a new pre-Linnaean description and thus a new taxon proposed by Joan Salvador. Moreover, Pourret published some taxa in his 
<taxonomicName authority="Narbonensis" authorityName="Narbonensis" box="[653,886,1103,1129]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chloris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[653,886,1103,1129]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Chloris Narbonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pourret, P. A." box="[900,1048,1103,1129]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="297 - 334" refId="ref6052" refString="Pourret, P. A. (1788) Extrait de la Chloris Narbonensis. Histoire et Memoires de l'Academie de Toulouse 3: 297 - 334." type="journal article" year="1788">Pourret 1788</bibRefCitation>
) as new species under the Linnaean system. Also, he sent some of these specimens to Lamarck in Paris and to Willdenow in Berlin and they are now preserved in the P and B-W herbaria (
<bibRefCitation author="Bonnet, E." box="[558,708,1173,1200]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="278 - 286" refId="ref4861" refString="Bonnet, E. (1916) Le cabinet d'histoire naturelle des freres Lomenie de Brienne, l'herbier de l'abbe Pourret et le legs fait par le Dr. Barbier au Museum en 1847. Histoire et documents. Bulletin du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle (Paris) 6: 278 - 286." type="journal article" year="1916">Bonnet 1916</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,258,2080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">
All three samples of Pourret’s plant show an unarmed, but for the rest normal 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1071,1215,1209,1235]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[1071,1215,1209,1235]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A." box="[1229,1447,1209,1235]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="204 - 208" refId="ref6719" refString="Van de Beek, A. (1979) Taxonomie en nomenclatuur van de Koebraam. Gorteria 9: 204 - 208." type="journal article" year="1979">Van de Beek (1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A." box="[136,194,1244,1271]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="33 - 51" refId="ref6742" refString="Van de Beek, A. (2016) Validations of the Rubus taxa in Tournefort's Institutiones and their Corollarium in later literature. Adansonia 38 (1): 33 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / a 2016 n 1 a 4" type="journal article" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
) thought it was collected in a natural habitat, because Pourret in his protologue does not refer to a garden. However, on the label of the specimen in the 
<collectingCountry box="[626,726,1279,1305]" name="El Salvador" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Salvador</collectingCountry>
collection is written: ‘In hortis colitur’ (handwritten by 
<collectingCountry box="[1335,1440,1279,1306]" name="El Salvador" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Salvador</collectingCountry>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[136,236,1314,1340]" name="El Salvador" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Salvador</collectingCountry>
also wrote ‘Romaguera de St. Francesc.’ Because this sample is not different from the other ones, these too, may have been collected in gardens of monasteries. The so called St. Francis blackberry is often bred in Franciscan monastery gardens because of its unarmed character. This plant was already known to early authors such as 
<bibRefCitation author="Tournefort, J. P." pageId="5" pageNumber="160" refId="ref6376" refString="Tournefort, J. P. (1700) Institutiones rei herbariae 1. Typographia Regia, Parisiis, 697 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 713" type="book" year="1700">Tournefort (1700)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Barrelier, J." box="[264,444,1420,1446]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" refId="ref4787" refString="Barrelier, J. (1714) Plantae per Galliam, Hispaniam et Italiam observatae iconibus aeneis exhibitae, ed. A. de Jussieu. Ganeau, Paris, 140 pp." type="book" year="1714">Barrelier (1714)</bibRefCitation>
and validated on the level of a variety by Weston: 
<taxonomicName authority="Weston (1770: 258)" authorityName="Weston" authorityPageNumber="258" authorityYear="1770" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="fruticosus" variety="inermis">
<emphasis box="[1004,1145,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. fruticosus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1199,1283,1421,1446]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">inermis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Weston, R." pageId="5" pageNumber="160" refId="ref6996" refString="Weston, R. (1770) Botanicus universalis et hortulanus, vol. 1. Bell, London, 384 pp." type="book" year="1770">Weston (1770: 258)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[253,356,1455,1481]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">lectotype</typeStatus>
of this name was designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A." box="[726,952,1455,1482]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="33 - 51" refId="ref6742" refString="Van de Beek, A. (2016) Validations of the Rubus taxa in Tournefort's Institutiones and their Corollarium in later literature. Adansonia 38 (1): 33 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / a 2016 n 1 a 4" type="journal article" year="2016">Van de Beek (2016)</bibRefCitation>
from a specimen preserved at P (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Tournefort 6078</emphasis>
, P-TRF) (
<figureCitation box="[307,375,1490,1516]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1799,1821]" captionTargetBox="[341,1245,190,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-34@4.[341,1245,190,1775]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lectotype of Rubus fruticosus var.inermis Weston (P, Tournefort 6078, P-TRF).Image courtesy of the herbariumP,reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585406/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,258,2080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[310,426,1526,1551]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[310,426,1526,1551]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was used once again by 
<bibRefCitation author="Willdenow, L." box="[712,979,1525,1552]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" refId="ref7045" refString="Willdenow, L. (1809) Enumeratio Plantarum Horti Regii Berolinensis. Taberna libraria scholae realis, Berolini, 592 pp." type="book" year="1809">Willdenow (1809: 549)</bibRefCitation>
. It is not based on a specimen of Pourret, but on another sample in B-W: BW09891010 (image available at https://herbarium.bgbm.org/object/BW09891010), from a plant in the hortus of 
<collectingRegion box="[463,536,1596,1622]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Berlin</collectingRegion>
, and so heterotypic with 
<taxonomicName authority="Pourr." authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[819,1014,1596,1622]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[819,935,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. inermis</emphasis>
Pourr.
</taxonomicName>
, and consequently as a later homonym illegitimate. 
<bibRefCitation author="Monasterio-Huelin, E. &amp; Weber, H. E." box="[278,680,1631,1658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="311 - 322" refId="ref5806" refString="Monasterio-Huelin, E. &amp; Weber, H. E. (1996) Taxonomy and nomenclature of Rubus ulmifolius and Rubus sanctus (Rosaceae). Edinburgh Journal of Botany 33: 311 - 322. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0960428600003759" type="journal article" year="1996">Monasterio-Huelin &amp; Weber (1996)</bibRefCitation>
identified it as 
<taxonomicName authority="Sudre (1909: 70)" authorityName="Sudre" authorityPageNumber="70" authorityYear="1909" box="[854,1420,1631,1658]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ulmifolius" variety="anoplosthyrsus">
<emphasis box="[854,998,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1053,1223,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">anoplosthyrsus</emphasis>
Sudre (1909: 70)
</taxonomicName>
so as conspecific with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[354,496,1666,1692]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[354,496,1666,1692]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A. &amp; Widrlechner, M. P." box="[508,900,1666,1693]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" pagination="67 - 98" refId="ref6791" refString="Van de Beek, A. &amp; Widrlechner, M. P. (2021) North American species of Rubus L. (Rosaceae) described from European botanical gardens (1789 - 1823). Adansonia 43 (8): 67 - 98. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / adansonia 2021 v 43 a 8" type="journal article" year="2021">Van de Beek &amp; Widrlechner (2021)</bibRefCitation>
accepted the identification by Monasterio-Huelin and Weber [
<typeStatus box="[266,385,1702,1728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Lectotype</typeStatus>
: B(BW09891010) (selected by Monaterio-Huelin &amp; Weber 1996: 316, pro 
<typeStatus box="[1214,1320,1701,1728]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">holotype</typeStatus>
)]. However, the specimen is somewhat different from the samples of Pourret and Tournefort: it has usually 3-foliate leaves of which the lower ones are often abaxially greenish grey (not white), with a more irregular serrature with long mucrons, small (almost) sessile lateral leaflets, ovate central leaflets, and often stipules with a large base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,258,2080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">
In the herbarium of Jussieu are 
<specimenCount box="[546,727,1842,1868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[765,881,1843,1868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[765,881,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. At one of the sheets (P-JUSS 14325) is a mixture of various species, partially with influence of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1753: 493)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="493" authorityYear="1753" box="[647,1011,1877,1904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caesius">
<emphasis box="[647,760,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">R. caesius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[767,1011,1877,1904]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" refId="ref5575" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species Plantarum 1. Salvius, Holmiae, 560 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 493)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimens on the other two sheets are more useful. One (P-JUSS 14333) looks like the specimens of Pourret and Tournefort, the other one (P-JUSS 14326) is similar to Willdenow’s plant. The labels do not provide further information, so that their origin is unknown. Later collections from the hortus in Paris are similar to the Willdenow plant (‘Cult. Paris. 
<date box="[1142,1300,1983,2010]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" value="1905-09-10">10 sept. 1905</date>
’, P02972716; 
<emphasis box="[136,291,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Delacourt s.n</emphasis>
., cult. Paris, 
<date box="[444,572,2018,2044]" pageId="5" pageNumber="160" value="1901-08-29">29.08.1901</date>
, P04173016; 
<emphasis box="[730,885,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="160">Delacourt s.n</emphasis>
., cult. ormament, Paris, 07.1895, P04181928 and P04181929).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585408" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5585408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585408/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="161" startId="6.[136,229,1928,1950]" targetBox="[151,1436,195,1903]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1451,1928,1986]" pageId="6" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,254,1928,1950]" pageId="6" pageNumber="161">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
Specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pourret" authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[389,605,1928,1949]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="6" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[389,527,1928,1949]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="161">Rubus inermis</emphasis>
Pourret
</taxonomicName>
preserved in the Salvador herbarium at BC (BC-Salvador 3833). Image courtesy of the herbarium BC, reproduced with permission.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,761]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">
So it seems that the form of Pourret was bred in gardens in 
<collectingCountry box="[839,906,158,184]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Spain</collectingCountry>
, the form of Willdenow in Berlin, and both forms also bred in Paris. 
<bibRefCitation author="Crane, M. B. &amp; Darlington, C. D." box="[349,659,194,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="241 - 276" refId="ref5021" refString="Crane, M. B. &amp; Darlington, C. D. (1927) The origin of new forms in Rubus I. Genetics 9: 241 - 276. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 01508292" type="journal article" year="1927">Crane &amp; Darlington (1927)</bibRefCitation>
researched the genetics of some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1037,1107,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1037,1107,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Rubus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa. They also checked what they called 
<taxonomicName box="[263,543,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ulmifolius" variety="inermis">
<emphasis box="[263,405,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[459,543,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Though the specimen that they published in their paper is poor it seems to be a 
<taxonomicName authority="Pourr." authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. inermis</emphasis>
Pourr.
</taxonomicName>
, with the better developed higher leaf with stalked lateral leaflets, lateral leaflets of normal size and an obovate central leaflet. The chromosome number is 14, as with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[855,998,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[855,998,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Michal Sochor (Olomouc) was so kind to check a sample of the Willdenow form, which is cultivated in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[911,981,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[911,981,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Rubus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
garden in Veenendaal (
<collectingCountry box="[1247,1441,338,365]" name="Netherlands" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">The Netherlands</collectingCountry>
). This one is tetraploid.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,761]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">
In sum, as far as conclusions can be drawn from present information, it appears that 
<taxonomicName authority="Pourret" authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[1173,1382,411,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[1173,1291,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. inermis</emphasis>
Pourret
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authority="Weston" authorityName="Weston" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="fruticosus" variety="inermis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. fruticosus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[306,390,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">inermis</emphasis>
Weston
</taxonomicName>
) is an unarmed form of the diploid 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[897,1042,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[897,1042,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Willd." authorityName="Willd." box="[1130,1326,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[1130,1247,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. inermis</emphasis>
Willd.
</taxonomicName>
is another, tetraploid taxon. Its precise status must be subject of further research.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,761]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">
<bibRefCitation author="Thunberg, C. P." box="[189,407,518,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" refId="ref6324" refString="Thunberg, C. P. (1813) Dissertatio botanico-medica de Rubo. Stenhammer &amp; Palmblad, Uppsala, 12 pp." type="book" year="1813">Thunberg (1813: 7)</bibRefCitation>
published once again a 
<taxonomicName box="[673,787,519,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[673,787,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[850,953,518,544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">lectotype</typeStatus>
of this name was designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A. &amp; Widrlechner, M. P." pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="67 - 98" refId="ref6791" refString="Van de Beek, A. &amp; Widrlechner, M. P. (2021) North American species of Rubus L. (Rosaceae) described from European botanical gardens (1789 - 1823). Adansonia 43 (8): 67 - 98. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / adansonia 2021 v 43 a 8" type="journal article" year="2021">Van de Beek &amp; Widrlechner (2021: 82)</bibRefCitation>
from a specimen kept at UPS (UPS-THUNB 12270) (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1136,554,581]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1834,1856]" captionTargetBox="[464,1123,785,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-319@7.[464,1123,785,1809]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Lectotype of Rubus inermis Thunberg (UPS-THUNB 12270). Image courtesy of the herbarium UPS, reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585411" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585411/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). This material is identical, though heterotypic, with 
<taxonomicName authority="Pourret (1788: 326)" authorityName="Pourret" authorityPageNumber="326" authorityYear="1788" box="[418,764,590,617]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[418,533,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. inermis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pourret, P. A." box="[540,764,590,617]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="297 - 334" refId="ref6052" refString="Pourret, P. A. (1788) Extrait de la Chloris Narbonensis. Histoire et Memoires de l'Academie de Toulouse 3: 297 - 334." type="journal article" year="1788">Pourret (1788: 326)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,761]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">
Both Willdenow and Thunberg related their plants to North America, where 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pourret" authorityYear="1788" box="[1040,1155,627,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[1040,1155,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not found (
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A. &amp; Widrlechner, M. P." pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="67 - 98" refId="ref6791" refString="Van de Beek, A. &amp; Widrlechner, M. P. (2021) North American species of Rubus L. (Rosaceae) described from European botanical gardens (1789 - 1823). Adansonia 43 (8): 67 - 98. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / adansonia 2021 v 43 a 8" type="journal article" year="2021">Van de Beek &amp; Widrlechner 2021</bibRefCitation>
). The confusion may be caused by a comparison with 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1753: 494)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="494" authorityYear="1753" box="[969,1372,662,689]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canadensis">
<emphasis box="[969,1123,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">R. canadensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1130,1372,662,689]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" refId="ref5575" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species Plantarum 1. Salvius, Holmiae, 560 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 494)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which was already made by Pourret on his label (‘an 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[653,777,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canadensis">
<emphasis box="[653,777,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">canadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ – maybe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[893,1017,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canadensis">
<emphasis box="[893,1017,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">canadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
?). 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1053,1294,698,725]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" refId="ref5575" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species Plantarum 1. Salvius, Holmiae, 560 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 494)</bibRefCitation>
mentions that species as unarmed and this may have caused the suggestion that unarmed blackberries come from America.
</paragraph>
